The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Kashmir groups

 Srinagar, July 1: A former chief justice of India, two former diplomats and an economist are tipped to head the working groups on Jammu and Kashmir.

 Former Chief Justice A.M. Ahmadi has been offered to head the panel that would deliberate on the special status of the state in the Indian Union.

 M.H. Ansari, a former diplomat who now heads the National Commission for Minorities, is likely to head the working group that will address the problem of rehabilitation.

 Another group, which will look to create people-to-people contact across the LoC, will be headed by former foreign secretary M.K. Rasgotra.

 The fourth group, to be headed by former RBI governor C. Rangarajan, will identify and create job opportunities in the state, besides balanced regional development.

 The fifth group on good governance is likely to be headed by N.C. Saxena, a former Planning Commission secretary.




